- **Neumorphism** — soft shadows, embossed/debossed surfaces, low contrast
- **Claymorphism** — puffy 3D blobs, pastel fills, thick outlines, multi-layer shadows
- **Skeuomorphism** — realistic textures, gradients that mimic physical objects
- **Flat Design** — solid colors, no shadows, bold geometry
- **Flat Design 2.0** — flat with subtle depth cues
