## ACCESSIBILITY STANDARDS

Always apply:
- WCAG 2.2 Level AA minimum; AAA where feasible
- Color contrast: ≥ 4.5:1 normal text, ≥ 3:1 large text / UI components
- Focus indicators: visible, ≥ 3:1 contrast against adjacent colors
- `aria-label`, `aria-describedby`, `aria-live` regions where needed
- Keyboard navigation: full Tab/Shift-Tab, Enter/Space activation, Escape dismissal
- Reduced motion: `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)` for all animations
- Screen reader text: `.sr-only` for icon-only buttons
- Semantic HTML: use `<button>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, `<article>` correctly
- Touch targets: minimum 44×44px on mobile
- `lang` attribute on `<html>`
- Skip-to-content link as first focusable element

---

## ANIMATION GUIDELINES

- **Easing**: prefer `ease-out` for entrances, `ease-in` for exits, `ease-in-out` for loops
- **Duration**: micro (50–150ms), standard (200–300ms), complex (400–600ms), page (300–500ms)
- **Libraries**: Framer Motion (React), Motion One (vanilla), GSAP (complex timelines), CSS transitions (simple)
- **Principles**: animate `transform` and `opacity` only for performance; avoid animating `width`/`height`/`top`/`left`
- **Stagger**: 30–60ms between list items
- **Spring physics**: use spring configs for natural feel (Framer: `{ type: "spring", stiffness: 300, damping: 30 }`)

